The ninth '''Women's Hockey World Cup Qualifier''' for the [[1998 Women's Hockey World Cup|World Cup]] in [[Utrecht (city)|Utrecht]], Netherlands was held in the ''Magamba Stadium'' in [[Harare, Zimbabwe]], from Friday 1 August to Tuesday 12 August 1997. Twelve nations took part, divided into two groups of six in the preliminary round. The top six teams joined Argentina, Olympic champions Australia, Germany, South Korea, the United States and hosts the Netherlands.

==Team squads==

=== {{fhw|Canada}} ===
<span style="font-size:90%"> [[Dana Anderson]], [[Sue Armstrong]], [[Nicole Colaco]], [[Lisa Faust]], [[Sarah Forbes (field hockey)|Sarah Forbes]] (gk), [[Aoibhinn Grimes]], [[Chris Hunter (hockey player)|Chris Hunter]], [[Laurelee Kopeck]], Amy MacFarlane, [[Karen MacNeill]], [[Veronica Planella]], [[Gillian Sewell]], [[Carla Somerville]], [[Sue Tingley]], [[Krista Thompson]] (gk), and [[Candy Thomson]]. Head Coach: [[Dru Marshall]].</span>

==={{fhw|India}}===
<span style="font-size:90%">  [[Tingonleima Chanu]] (gk), [[Helen Mary]] (gk), [[Sandeep Kaur (field hockey)|Sandeep Khaur]], [[Shashi Bala]] (captain), [[Maristella Tirkey]], [[Mukta Xalco]], [[Sita Gussain]], [[Sumrai Tete]], [[Sunita Dalal]], [[Nidhi Khullar]], [[Manjinder Kaur]], [[Pritam Thakran]], [[Kamala Dalal]], [[Suraj Lata Devi]], [[Jyoti Sunita Kullu]], and [[Ferdina Ekka]]. Head coach: [[Balbir Singh Kular|Balbir Singh]].</span>

