The '''Burkinabé Football Federation''' ({{lang-fr|Fédération Burkinabé de Football, FBF}}) is the governing body of [[Football (soccer)|football]] in [[Burkina Faso]]. Their offices are based in the capital city Ouagadougou. The president of the federation is Sita Sangaré.

==History==
It was founded in 1959, and affiliated to [[FIFA]] and to [[Confederation of African Football|CAF]] in 1964. It organizes the national football league and the [[Burkina Faso national football team|national team]].<ref>[http://www.cafonline.com/association/burkina-faso  Burkina Faso] at CAF Online</ref>

==Staff==
*President: Sita Sangaré<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/associations/association=bfa/index.html Burkina Faso] at the [[FIFA]] website.</ref>
*Vice President: Laurent Blaise Kaboré
*General Secretary: Boureima Balima
*Treasurer: Idrissa Kafando
*Technical Director: Ousmane Savadogo
*Men's Coach:  [Paulo Duarte]
*Media Officer:	Gabriel Nacoulma
*Referee Coordinator: David Yaméogo

