{{Infobox country at games | NOC = KUW | NOCname = [[Kuwait Olympic Committee]] | oldcode = | year = 1998 | date = | games = Asian Games | location = [[Bangkok]] | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | officials = | gold = 4 | silver = 6 | bronze = 4 | rank = 14 | appearances = auto | seealso = {{flagIOC2|IOC|2010 Asian Games}} (2010) | website = }}
'''[[Kuwait]]''' participated in the [[1998 Asian Games]] held in [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]] from December 6, 1998 to December 20, 1998. Athletes from Kuwait succeeded in winning 4 golds, 6 silvers and 4 bronzes, making total 14 medals. Kuwait finished fourteenth in a medal table.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ocasia.org/Game/MWinner.aspx?AMWCode=17&GCode=1 | title=Over all medal standings &ndash; Bangkok 1998 | publisher=ocasia.org | work=[[Olympic Council of Asia]] | accessdate=June 4, 2011}}</ref>
