{{Infobox swimming association |Logo=Swimming Federation of BiH Logo.jpg |Founded=2002 <ref>[http://www.lenmagazine.com/len/len.head.page?nodeid=327 Swimming Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina], LEN Magazine</ref> |FINA affiliation=2002 |Region=[[Ligue Européenne de Natation|LEN]] |Region affiliation=2002 |President=[http://www.lenmagazine.com/len/len.head.page?nodeid=327 Milorad Vulić] |Website=[http://www.plivackisavezbih.ba plivackisavezbih.ba] }}
The '''Swimming Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina''' ([[Bosnian language|Bosnian]], [[Croatian language|Croatian]] and [[Serbian language|Serbian]]: Plivački savez Bosne i Hercegovine / Пливачки савез Босне и Херцеговине) is the governing body of swimming in Bosnia. It is a non-profit organization that was founded on December 1, 2002 at a meeting at the [[Olympic Committee of Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. It is both a member of [[Ligue Européenne de Natation|LEN]] and [[FINA]].<ref>[http://www.plivackisavez.ba/index.php?module=dokumenti Statut], plivackisavez.ba (bs)</ref>
==Member clubs== {{As of|2010|2}} there are 15 member clubs.<ref>[http://www.plivackisavez.ba/index.php?module=clanovi&part=klubovi Klubovi], plivackisavez.ba (bs)</ref>
{{col-begin}} {{col-break}} * APK 22. april, [[Banja Luka]] * PK Banja Luka, Banja Luka * PK Mladost, Banja Luka * PK Olymp, Banja Luka * PK Vrbas, Banja Luka * PK Savski galeb, [[Brčko (city)|Brčko]] {{col-break}} * PK Lisičići, [[Konjic]] * PK Delfin, [[Laktaši]] * PK Galeb-Gikil, [[Lukavac]] * PK Velež, [[Mostar]] * [[PK Bosna]], [[Sarajevo]] {{col-break}} * PK Leotar, [[Trebinje]] * Gradski Klub Vodenih Sportova "Jedinstvo"[[Tuzla]] * PK Aquatech, [[Tuzla]] * PK Sloboda, Tuzla * PK Zmaj-Alpamm, Tuzla * PK Željezara, [[Zenica]] {{col-end}}
